1. We derive a substantial portion of our revenue from a limited number of customers. Our top 10 customers accounted for 46.00%, 56.82% and 66.72%, of our revenue from operations (continuing operations) in Fiscals 2025, 2024 and 2023, respectively. Loss of relationship with any of these customers or delays or reductions in their orders may have an adverse effect on our business, results of operations, financial condition and cash flows;
2. We depend on a few suppliers for the supply of our primary raw materials and any disruption in the supply or increase in the prices of raw materials could adversely affect our business, financial condition, results of operations and cash flows. Our top 10 suppliers accounted for 83.22%, 74.63% and 79.53% of our total cost of raw materials in Fiscals 2025, 2024 and 2023, respectively;
3. A significant portion of our revenue is derived from the sale of overhead conductors, which accounted for 63.94%, 62.83% and 58.37% of our revenue from operations (continuing operations) in Fiscals 2025, 2024 and 2023, respectively. Any adverse changes in the conditions affecting overhead conductor market may adversely impact our business, financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and prospects;
4. Our manufacturing facilities are subject to operating risks. Any disruption, breakdown or shutdown of our manufacturing facilities may have an adverse effect on our business, financial condition, results of operations and cash flows;
5. We derive a portion of our segment revenue from external turnover from continuing operations outside India in accordance with Ind AS 108 'Operating Segments' (20.19%, 33.71% and 35.99% of our revenue from operations (continuing operations) in Fiscal 2025, 2024 and 2023 respectively). Any adverse events in the countries where we export our products could have an adverse impact on our business, results of operations, financial condition and cash flows;
6. Our products are subject to stringent quality requirements. Any product defects or failure by us or our raw material suppliers to comply with these quality standards could lead to the cancellation of existing and future orders, product recalls warranty claims and exposure to potential product liability claims;
7. Our Company, Promoters, Directors, Subsidiaries and Group Companies are involved in certain legal and regulatory proceedings. Any adverse decision in such proceedings may have an adverse effect on our business, financial condition, cash flows and results of operations;
8. Our inability to meet our obligations, including financial and other covenants under our debt financing arrangements could adversely affect our business, results of operations, financial condition and cash flows;
9. We require certain licenses, permits and approvals in the ordinary course of business, and the failure to obtain or retain them in a timely manner may materially adversely affect our operations; and
10. We operate in a competitive business environment. Failure to compete effectively against our competitors and new entrants to the industry may adversely affect our business, financial condition and results of operations.
